<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/885</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22T20:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2981. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 1691. Your 1895, Embassy 3814, November 18, 5 p.m. We doubt
                                advisability of sending letter as suggested which appears to <pb facs="0740" n="1574" xml:id="pg_1574"/> savor of interference in
                                internal affairs of Holland. Our recent reports of domestic
                                situation of Holland indicate that the situation, which doubtless
                                prompted suggestion, has now passed its critical stage. We assume
                                that were present Government replaced by one which Associated
                                Governments did not recognize, we would automatically be released
                                from compliance with agreement and that it could readily be arranged
                                informally that this be understood in Holland.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>